cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the security of critical infrastructure, specifically power, natural gas, and water systems, which are all cyber-physical systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a game-theoretic framework to analyze the interactions between the attacker and the administrator, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also uses a state-space model to capture the interdependence between the different components of the infrastructure, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also proposes a method for assigning protection levels to sensors based on their importance in the state estimation process, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with cyber attacks on interdependent systems, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
